quran[9]{c,v,t}:
  4,66,"Had we laid down such a law for them as \"Kill yourselves, or abandon your dwellings,\" but few of them would have done it. But had they done that to which they were exhorted, better and it been for them, and stronger for the confirmation of their faith"
  4,67,In that case we had surely given them from ourself a great recompense
  4,68,and on the straight path should we surely have guided them
  4,69,"And whoever shall obey God and the Apostle, these shall be with those of the Prophets, and of the Sincere, and of the Martyrs, and of the Just, to whom God hath been gracious. These are a goodly band"
  4,70,This is the bounty of God; and in knowledge doth God suffice
  4,71,"O ye who believe! make use of precautions; and advance in detachments, or , advance in a body"
  4,72,"There is of you who will be a laggard: and if a reverse befall you he saith, \"Now hath God dealt graciously with me, since I was not with you in the fight"
  4,73,"But if a success from God betide you, he will say, as if there had never been any friendship between you and him, \"Would I had been with them! a rich prize should I have won"
  4,74,"Let those then fight on the path of God, who barter this present life for that which is to come; for whoever fighteth on God's path, whether he be slain or conquer, we will in the end give him a great reward"